Below is a comprehensive list of entry-level, safe, and client-ready services a solo cybersecurity professional can offer to small businesses. These focus on practical value without requiring enterprise-grade tooling.

✅ Entry-Level Cybersecurity Services for Small Businesses
1. Security Assessments (Foundational)

Basic security posture review

Workstation & device security check (OS updates, antivirus status, configurations)

User account & permission review

Cloud account security check (Microsoft 365, Google Workspace, etc.)

Vulnerability scanning (using safe, automated scanners—no exploit work)

2. Policy & Best-Practice Development

Acceptable use policies (AUP)

Password & authentication policy

Remote work & device usage guidelines

Data handling & classification guidelines

Security awareness onboarding materials

3. Cyber Hygiene Improvements

Password manager setup & rollout

Multi-factor authentication (MFA) implementation

Basic network hardening (router configuration, guest networks, DNS filtering)

Backup strategy creation (local + cloud options)

Secure laptop/phone configuration

4. Employee Security Training

Basic cybersecurity awareness workshop

Phishing recognition training

Safe internet & email usage training

Incident reporting process training

Quarterly refresher training

5. Data Protection & Continuity

Backup system selection and deployment

Disaster recovery plan for small environments

Ransomware protection setup (with reputable tools)

Data retention & archiving best practices

6. Cloud Security Services

Microsoft 365 security hardening

Google Workspace security configuration

Secure file sharing setup

Access control review & cleanup

Cloud backup configuration

7. Network & Endpoint Security

Antivirus/endpoint protection setup

Firewall rule review (small office routers)

Secure Wi-Fi configuration

DNS security filtering setup (e.g., Quad9, Cisco Umbrella basic)

8. Monitoring & Maintenance (Lightweight)

Patch & update monitoring

Quarterly security health checks

License tracking (antivirus, cloud subscriptions)

Routine backup integrity testing

9. Compliance-Lite (Non-certifying)

(Not formal audits, but preparation support.)

Basic GDPR alignment steps

HIPAA readiness guidance (not certification)

Cyber insurance questionnaire assistance

Security policy documentation packages

10. Incident Support (Non-forensic)

Basic incident triage

Containment assistance (account lockouts, password resets)

Cleanup guidance (malware removal, credential rotation)

Post-incident recommendations

⭐ Optional “Add-On” Services (Still Entry-Friendly)

Password vault setup for individuals

Website security basics (SSL, admin account hardening)

Secure email setup (DMARC, SPF, DKIM configuration)

Device lifecycle security (secure wipe + disposal)

Vendor security evaluation (quick reviews of tools/services clients want to adopt)

